On January 12, 2023, 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps will have 1.27 million inpatients with COVID-19 infection, and 104018 patients with severe (including critical diseases), including 7357 patients with severe COVID-19 infection and 96661 patients with severe underlying diseases combined with COVID-19 infection. From December 8, 2022 to January 12, 2023, the medical institutions of 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have accumulated 59938 COVID-19 infection related deaths in hospitals, including 5503 deaths due to respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection, and 54435 deaths due to underlying diseases combined with COVID-19 infection.

On January 19, there were 471739 hospitalized cases of COVID-19 infection in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, and 51683 severe cases, including 3874 severe cases of COVID-19 infection and 47809 severe cases of basic diseases combined with COVID-19 infection. From January 13 to 19, there were 12658 COVID-19 infection related deaths in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and medical institutions of Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, including 681 deaths from respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection and 11977 deaths from basic diseases combined with COVID-19 infection.

On January 26, there were 215958 hospitalized cases of COVID-19 infection in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, and 26156 severe cases, including 1894 severe cases of COVID-19 infection and 24262 severe cases of basic diseases complicated with COVID-19 infection. From January 20 to 26, medical institutions in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps accumulated 6364 deaths related to COVID-19 infection in hospitals, including 289 deaths from respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection and 6075 deaths from basic diseases combined with COVID-19 infection.

On February 2, there were 98742 hospitalized cases of COVID-19 infection in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, and 7918 severe cases, including 653 severe cases of COVID-19 infection and 7265 severe cases of basic diseases complicated with COVID-19 infection. From January 27 to February 2, the medical institutions of 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps accumulated 3278 COVID-19 infection related deaths in hospitals, including 131 deaths due to respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection and 3147 deaths due to underlying diseases combined with COVID-19 infection.

On February 9, there were 37611 inpatients and 424 severe cases of COVID-19 infection in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, including 46 severe cases of COVID-19 infection and 378 severe cases of basic diseases complicated with COVID-19 infection. From February 3 to February 9, medical institutions in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps accumulated 912 COVID-19 infection related deaths in hospitals, including 27 deaths due to respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection, and 885 deaths due to underlying diseases combined with COVID-19 infection.

From December 8, 2022 to January 26, 2023, medical institutions in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have accumulated 83150 COVID-19 infection related deaths in hospitals, including 6631 deaths from respiratory failure caused by COVID-19 infection, and 76519 deaths from underlying diseases combined with COVID-19 infection
